wikipedia_page.main: Christina of Markyate was born with the name Theodora in Huntingdon, England, about 1096–1098 and died about 1155. She was an anchoress, who came from a wealthy English family trying to accommodate with the Normans at that time. She was niece of the powerful Bishop Ranulf Flambard. She later became the prioress of a community of nuns.
